article.headline: E. Washington 73, Texas-Arlington 70
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- Benny Valentine scored 24 of his 28 points in the second half and Eastern Washington survived poor foul shooting to beat Texas Arlington 73-70 Saturday night. Milan Stanojevic added 17 points and, Brandon Moore 16 points and 11 rebounds for the Eagles (2-1). The Mavericks (2-1), led by Anthony Vereen's 19 points and 12 rebounds, had a chance to tie the score at the end of the game, but Jeremy Smith's buzzer-beating, 3-point attempt bounced around the rim before falling out. The Eagles held a 72-67 lead after Valentine hit 1-of-2 from the free-throw line with 11.6 seconds left. Texas-Arlington's Brandon Long answered with a long 3-pointer in front of two defenders to pull the Mavericks to within 72-70 with 6.7 seconds remaining. Valentine was fouled again and again converted 1-of-2 to increase the Eagles' lead to 73-70, setting up Smith's game-tying attempt.
